36:57.998 --> 36:59.826
[pancake sizzling]

37:04.961 --> 37:07.181
Do you think it's even
his parents' house?

37:07.181 --> 37:08.661
It was 200 euros total.

37:08.661 --> 37:10.576
I'm not asking any questions.

37:10.576 --> 37:12.795
[picaresque guitar]

37:12.795 --> 37:16.059
He knows we're talking about
him, change the subject please.

37:17.147 --> 37:18.236
I have to tell you something.

37:19.715 --> 37:21.761
Oh shit, you're pregnant.

37:21.761 --> 37:23.980
- No, no.
- [Leo sighs relief]

37:27.114 --> 37:28.855
Amber Jane cheated on Rome.

37:30.509 --> 37:31.336
I know.

37:33.251 --> 37:34.164
[pancake splats]

37:35.557 --> 37:37.559
You guys are all real
fucking assholes.

37:39.344 --> 37:40.867
You do?

37:40.867 --> 37:43.957
Yep, I investigated,
and I found out.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.480
Wasn't hard either.

37:45.480 --> 37:46.829
She didn't exactly,
conceal her cards.

37:46.829 --> 37:48.309
So Rome knows?

37:48.309 --> 37:51.269
No. And I'm not
telling him either.

37:51.269 --> 37:54.272
They're not together so,
she can't hurt him anymore.

37:54.272 --> 37:56.056
But if they get back together?

37:57.144 --> 37:58.798
Did you see that girl Giorgia?

38:01.104 --> 38:03.411
Once you go Giorgia,
you can't go Amber Jane.

38:05.326 --> 38:06.849
She is super hot.

38:06.849 --> 38:07.676
[light upbeat music]

38:12.725 --> 38:14.117
[Amber Jane sighing]

38:15.380 --> 38:17.251
[light upbeat music]

38:25.912 --> 38:26.739
Hey, Rome.

38:27.827 --> 38:29.132
Are you being nice to me?

38:30.482 --> 38:32.179
Has the world
turned upside down?

38:33.572 --> 38:36.314
Get it? Nah, you don't get it.

38:36.314 --> 38:37.750
Don't make me laugh.

38:42.145 --> 38:43.799
You want a pancake?

38:43.799 --> 38:45.540
Hey, no thank you.

38:45.540 --> 38:48.500
All right, as of tomorrow,
no more breakfast.

38:48.500 --> 38:50.502
Unappreciative assholes.

38:51.851 --> 38:53.069
[sighs]

38:53.069 --> 38:55.420
So, what are we doing today?

38:58.379 --> 39:01.208
Okay, don't answer me, I'll
just go hang out with Dan.

39:01.208 --> 39:03.079
- He went nuts last night.
- Really?

39:03.079 --> 39:04.254
- No.
- Oh.

39:04.254 --> 39:06.779
Dan doesn't know how to live.

39:06.779 --> 39:08.998
He's wasting his life
in front of a computer.

39:08.998 --> 39:11.392
I don't know, maybe
that's just his M.O,

39:11.392 --> 39:12.567
he seems pretty happy.

39:12.567 --> 39:15.614
You should go and see Giorgia.

39:15.614 --> 39:16.658
Giorgia.

39:18.573 --> 39:20.053
I could go bug her at work.

39:21.750 --> 39:22.577
[footsteps fading]

39:22.577 --> 39:23.404
[birds chirping]

39:25.711 --> 39:26.799
[leaves rustling]

39:29.149 --> 39:30.368
Can I talk to you?

39:33.414 --> 39:36.504
[introspective music]

39:36.504 --> 39:37.723
[birds chirping]

39:38.941 --> 39:42.597
[introspective music]

39:52.912 --> 39:54.914
[Amber Jane] Chapel tower.

39:54.914 --> 39:56.263
[Rome] Twice.

39:56.263 --> 39:57.612
Music rooms.

39:57.612 --> 39:59.875
[Amber Jane] Many times.
[both chuckle]

40:01.355 --> 40:02.878
Do you remember the very
first time we kissed?

40:02.878 --> 40:06.882
Of course, it was
freshman year, snowing.

40:08.362 --> 40:09.885
You know I made it
to check-in on time?

40:10.886 --> 40:12.845
From Willard Hall,

40:12.845 --> 40:14.760
in one minute,

40:14.760 --> 40:15.761
I don't think I'll run half
as fast the rest of my life.

40:15.761 --> 40:16.892
Rome, I miss you.

40:21.593 --> 40:23.203
This whole semester has been--

40:25.597 --> 40:27.729
How can you say
something like that?

40:27.729 --> 40:30.471
And then at times be so
scathing, denigrating.

40:30.471 --> 40:32.908
Stop using SAT words.

40:32.908 --> 40:36.434
They're not SAT words,
they're just, words.

40:37.913 --> 40:39.698
You say don't love me
anymore, Amber Jane.

40:41.003 --> 40:42.352
And now you say you miss me.

40:43.658 --> 40:46.356
It's, it's a little crazy.

40:46.356 --> 40:47.183
It is.

40:48.228 --> 40:49.055
It is.

40:52.058 --> 40:53.973
I'm sorry, Rome.

40:55.409 --> 40:57.237
[introspective music]

41:12.905 --> 41:13.906
I need to know.

41:15.342 --> 41:17.126
What's the real
story with Leonardo?

41:18.388 --> 41:19.694
You're always so jealous.

41:22.697 --> 41:24.046
Listen, it's fine.

41:26.396 --> 41:30.052
I forgive your jealousy, it
just means you care about me.

41:33.316 --> 41:34.840
Let's go back to the villa.

41:37.059 --> 41:38.844
I want you to ravish me.

41:40.410 --> 41:42.064
[whispers] It's an
eighth of a villa.

41:42.064 --> 41:44.023
Shh.

41:44.023 --> 41:47.113
[whimsical music]

41:47.113 --> 41:49.724
[footsteps approaching]

41:49.724 --> 41:51.552
[birds chirping]

41:53.902 --> 41:55.382
[bell ringing]

41:58.080 --> 42:00.300
[Leo moaning]

42:00.300 --> 42:02.215
[Leo] Am I doing this right?

42:02.215 --> 42:03.042
Perfect.

42:05.740 --> 42:06.959
Maybe a little faster?

42:08.047 --> 42:09.222
Okay.

42:09.222 --> 42:10.528
[moaning]
[bed creaking]

42:11.485 --> 42:12.878
[both moaning]

42:12.878 --> 42:14.836
- Perfect
- I need to slow down.

42:16.882 --> 42:18.623
[frame creaking]

42:20.363 --> 42:22.365
[bed clattering]
[both panting]

42:22.365 --> 42:24.150
[foot thud]

42:24.150 --> 42:25.934
[Leo] They banned this in Spain.
They banned this in Spain.

42:25.934 --> 42:28.415
Charles Dickens,
Charles Dickens,

42:28.415 --> 42:30.373
Charles Dickens!

42:30.373 --> 42:31.200
Shit.

42:34.639 --> 42:36.902
[whimsical music]

42:46.868 --> 42:47.869
[door shuts]

43:01.361 --> 43:02.188
[wood creaks]

43:12.328 --> 43:13.503
[deep sighing]

43:18.813 --> 43:20.293
[grunts, taps]

43:26.038 --> 43:28.693
[frenzied footsteps]

43:34.046 --> 43:34.960
[door slams]

43:35.961 --> 43:39.312
[Claire laughing]

43:39.312 --> 43:40.618
She's seriously gotten
dumber since she started

43:40.618 --> 43:42.097
hooking up with Leo.

43:42.097 --> 43:43.272
[Claire laughing]

43:43.272 --> 43:45.013
It's like the head of a beluga.

43:45.013 --> 43:46.536
[Claire laughing]

43:46.536 --> 43:49.061
I bet he'll die during
his gap year. O.D.

43:50.149 --> 43:51.324
He's my best friend.

43:51.324 --> 43:52.847
I know but, you'll see.

43:54.240 --> 43:55.633
Fine for high school
but, you know.

43:57.286 --> 43:58.244
I don't actually.

43:59.985 --> 44:03.249
I don't think he's bright
enough for you, okay?

44:03.249 --> 44:05.164
It's a compliment.

44:05.164 --> 44:08.341
You should be friends with
people of a certain level.

44:08.341 --> 44:09.168
You like it?

44:10.560 --> 44:12.606
I got it at your
little friend's store.

44:12.606 --> 44:14.826
Cheap stuff but
what can you expect?

44:14.826 --> 44:17.176
It's Santa Lorena, not Milan.

44:19.744 --> 44:23.008
Come here, I want
you to rip it off me.

44:26.533 --> 44:30.145
No, no.

44:35.629 --> 44:37.718
Look we broke up,
Amber Jane, okay?

44:38.676 --> 44:39.633
You broke up with me.

44:41.200 --> 44:42.810
I think we should
stay broken up.

44:44.682 --> 44:46.596
[sighing]

44:46.596 --> 44:50.035
I mean, how can you be so
disparaging of your friend

44:50.035 --> 44:51.210
and my best friend?

44:53.429 --> 44:56.606
No, I don't want to rip
off Giorgia's swimsuit.

45:00.219 --> 45:01.176
This was a mistake.

45:04.484 --> 45:06.791
[gasping]

45:06.791 --> 45:08.357
[door slams]

45:08.357 --> 45:11.143
[indignant panting]

45:11.143 --> 45:14.973
You're oblivious, stupid.

45:14.973 --> 45:16.626
[headrest bangs]

45:16.626 --> 45:18.628
[pillow thud]
[indistinct grievance]

45:19.673 --> 45:20.500
[Amber Jane] Rome?

45:22.632 --> 45:25.026
Pssst, what's going on?

45:27.333 --> 45:28.160
Nothing.

45:29.814 --> 45:31.729
I think I'm finally
over Amber Jane.

45:33.774 --> 45:34.644
Come in.

45:36.255 --> 45:37.299
Centipede style?

45:38.431 --> 45:41.260
[upbeat music]

45:48.920 --> 45:50.748
It's dick time.

45:50.748 --> 45:52.662
[singing in Italian]

45:56.666 --> 45:58.190
[Unremarkable Dan] Get
the fuck off of me!

45:59.931 --> 46:01.889
[footsteps pattering]
[both struggling]

46:01.889 --> 46:03.151
[grunting]

46:03.151 --> 46:04.239
[Schmae] Fucking bitch.

46:05.763 --> 46:06.894
Fucking bitch!

46:08.591 --> 46:11.159
[upbeat music]
[singing in Italian]

46:19.428 --> 46:21.953
I know, I'm more
off-putting during the day.

46:24.042 --> 46:25.434
I have something for you.

46:30.918 --> 46:32.485
I love it.

46:32.485 --> 46:34.139
[bells ringing]

46:34.139 --> 46:36.358
[Rome] I need to confess
something that happened.

46:36.358 --> 46:41.363
This morning, Amber Jane, my
ex, she wanted to talk, so.

46:42.800 --> 46:46.586
We talked about stuff,
the past, et cetera.

46:48.370 --> 46:52.810
And then she kissed me.
And I resisted, at first,

46:54.289 --> 46:57.205
but then I kissed her
back for a little while.

46:59.599 --> 47:01.340
But then I realized, you
know, it was a big mistake

47:01.340 --> 47:03.168
and we're not right
for each other.

47:03.168 --> 47:04.909
Look, I know you probably
don't care about this,

47:04.909 --> 47:06.475
'cause you're super
liberal about these things,

47:06.475 --> 47:09.478
but I just wanted
to tell you, since.

47:09.478 --> 47:11.611
You know, we've been hanging
out these last two days

47:11.611 --> 47:12.786
which has been great.

47:14.135 --> 47:15.571
I'm not with her anymore.

47:17.922 --> 47:19.445
I'm sorry.

47:19.445 --> 47:21.142
We're not boyfriend
and girlfriend.

47:21.142 --> 47:25.103
I mean, you don't, you
don't have to apologize.

47:27.845 --> 47:28.671
Okay.

47:30.848 --> 47:33.807
Can I still see you
today or maybe tonight?

47:33.807 --> 47:34.634
Not today.

47:35.765 --> 47:37.158
[Giorgia] I'll see you around.

47:41.162 --> 47:43.338
Thank you for the drawing.

47:43.338 --> 47:45.906
[gentle music]

47:58.788 --> 47:59.789
[sighing]

47:59.789 --> 48:02.357
[gentle music]

48:11.497 --> 48:13.847
[sea lapping]

48:59.066 --> 49:00.024
You keep a diary?

49:00.981 --> 49:02.461
Kind of.

49:02.461 --> 49:04.942
With like, your feelings?

49:04.942 --> 49:06.552
[Claire chuckling]

49:06.552 --> 49:08.423
Sometimes.

49:08.423 --> 49:12.210
Usually events, special
times I want to remember.

49:12.210 --> 49:13.211
Can I read it?

49:14.429 --> 49:15.953
You can read this page.

49:17.302 --> 49:18.781
You're in it.

49:18.781 --> 49:20.435
[Claire chuckling]

49:20.435 --> 49:21.959
You see, in 10 years,

49:21.959 --> 49:24.526
I would have forgotten
all about this trip.

49:24.526 --> 49:28.530
Or maybe have some vague
memory of it, you know,

49:28.530 --> 49:30.010
the vacation with the Vespa.

49:30.010 --> 49:31.838
[Claire chuckling]

49:31.838 --> 49:35.885
So this diary is a sort
of door to the past.

49:36.886 --> 49:38.062
A way to access it.

49:39.846 --> 49:42.631
And when I open to this page,

49:42.631 --> 49:43.458
I'll remember,

49:45.460 --> 49:48.072
the Vespa and the spritz,

49:48.072 --> 49:50.248
sunbathing with Amber Jane.

49:51.858 --> 49:52.859
Leo.

49:55.949 --> 49:58.734
You should try keeping a
diary during your gap year.

49:58.734 --> 49:59.953
Yeah, maybe.

50:02.956 --> 50:04.305
Can I read the whole thing?

50:04.305 --> 50:06.046
No.

50:06.046 --> 50:08.396
There are definitely
embarrassing things in here.

50:08.396 --> 50:09.963
Boys from the past.

50:09.963 --> 50:10.964
[both laughing]

50:10.964 --> 50:12.226
Now I have to read it.

50:12.226 --> 50:14.011
No.
[Claire laughing]

50:14.011 --> 50:15.316
I have a proposition.

50:17.014 --> 50:20.191
I'll open the diary and whatever
I land on, I can read it.

50:22.889 --> 50:23.803
Fine.

50:25.239 --> 50:26.197
[Claire titters]

50:30.070 --> 50:32.551
- Oh no no no that's too
embarrassing. - Wait wait wait.

50:35.858 --> 50:38.252
[wistful music]

50:38.252 --> 50:40.863
A library, with walnut floors.

50:40.863 --> 50:42.082
[water splashing]

50:42.082 --> 50:43.736
All I wanted was
to get with her.

50:45.390 --> 50:48.349
Now that I did, I
realize I don't have her.

50:50.047 --> 50:53.137
Soon, I'll just be
another guy from the past.

50:55.008 --> 50:56.314
A page in her diary.

50:58.490 --> 51:00.057
I think you should appreciate

51:00.057 --> 51:01.710
that she even lets
you talk to her.

51:01.710 --> 51:04.365
The fact you've
been inside her...

51:05.671 --> 51:07.760
blows my fucking mind.

51:09.457 --> 51:11.068
You want too much.

51:11.068 --> 51:13.592
But hey, if you really want it,

51:13.592 --> 51:15.594
you're gonna have
to work for it.

51:15.594 --> 51:16.682
[tapping]

51:18.249 --> 51:19.815
You're wise.

51:19.815 --> 51:23.732
If I were really wise,
I'd be fucking rich.

51:23.732 --> 51:25.647
[film camera rolling]

51:32.785 --> 51:34.526
[memory chimes]

51:37.181 --> 51:40.053
[water splashing]

51:49.106 --> 51:52.631
[tense suspenseful music]

52:04.730 --> 52:05.687
[pebbles moving]

52:08.821 --> 52:10.127
Vicente! Vicente!

52:10.127 --> 52:11.824
Don't do it!

52:11.824 --> 52:13.695
I have nothing to live for.

52:13.695 --> 52:14.914
Stop, stop okay?

52:14.914 --> 52:16.263
[Rome panting]

52:17.438 --> 52:18.439
[tense suspenseful music]

52:18.439 --> 52:21.138
Look, I'll do it, okay?

52:22.574 --> 52:27.100
I'll perform the,
Estocada on you, okay?

52:27.100 --> 52:28.406
So you can die with honor.

52:30.451 --> 52:31.365
Like the bulls?

52:32.540 --> 52:34.238
Yeah, yeah like the bulls.

52:37.589 --> 52:38.503
I am listening.

52:40.244 --> 52:43.421
I can stab you through
the nape, into your heart.

52:43.421 --> 52:44.726
That's not a problem.

52:46.511 --> 52:50.297
But, first I've gotta go
back and change, you know?

52:50.297 --> 52:53.170
Ah, I have to be wearing my
finest attire, to honor you.

52:53.170 --> 52:55.041
You know. Like you
honor the bulls.

52:55.041 --> 52:56.825
Of course, of course.

52:56.825 --> 52:59.654
And plus, I mean, it's
flood tide right now, right?

52:59.654 --> 53:01.482
So you're body's just
gonna end up on the rocks.

53:01.482 --> 53:03.397
Wait for the tide
to be going out

53:03.397 --> 53:05.921
so you'll be carried into the
Mediterranean Sea, with honor.

53:05.921 --> 53:06.879
Like the beluga?

53:08.576 --> 53:11.231
Yeah, yeah like the beluga.

53:11.231 --> 53:13.015
You know, and there's
also less chance

53:13.015 --> 53:14.669
of me being arrested for
homicide which is always a plus.

53:17.324 --> 53:18.282
[inhales deeply]
Okay.

53:19.761 --> 53:22.677
Estocada, when the
lower arc of the sun

53:22.677 --> 53:24.679
is 15 degrees from horizon.

53:25.767 --> 53:26.594
Okay.

53:28.117 --> 53:31.425
And hey, if you don't
kill me, I am jumping.

53:33.819 --> 53:35.864
Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

53:37.257 --> 53:38.737
[tense dramatic music]

53:38.737 --> 53:39.868
[footsteps approaching]

53:39.868 --> 53:42.131
What the fuck.

53:42.131 --> 53:44.221
[tense dramatic music]

53:47.876 --> 53:51.837
[fast running patter]

53:53.230 --> 53:54.318
[raps on glass]

53:56.624 --> 53:58.322
Rome please, not today.

53:59.758 --> 54:00.933
[Rome heaving]

54:00.933 --> 54:03.283
This has nothing to do with us.

54:03.283 --> 54:06.895
Vicente Caudales, is
going to kill himself.

54:07.940 --> 54:09.115
[footsteps approaching]

54:09.115 --> 54:10.943
[tense dramatic music]

54:44.629 --> 54:45.804
[door booming]

54:45.804 --> 54:47.109
I came super super quick.

54:53.855 --> 54:55.030
Where's Amber Jane?

54:55.030 --> 54:56.684
[spiritual music]

55:08.914 --> 55:10.089
Whatever.

55:10.089 --> 55:12.004
Alright, here's the deal.

55:12.004 --> 55:15.573
Vicente Caudales is
planning to kill himself.

55:15.573 --> 55:17.618
Now, I bought us some more time,

55:17.618 --> 55:19.968
because I promised I'm
gonna murder him myself.

55:19.968 --> 55:22.057
I do not intend to go
forward with that promise.

55:22.057 --> 55:24.103
By which point, he's gonna
proceed with his plan.

55:24.103 --> 55:25.452
Now what we need to do,

55:25.452 --> 55:27.324
is help Vicente change his mind.

55:28.368 --> 55:30.327
Find meaning in his life.

55:30.327 --> 55:32.720
Otherwise, even if
we save him today,

55:32.720 --> 55:34.896
he's just gonna kill
himself any other day.

55:34.896 --> 55:38.639
Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday.

55:38.639 --> 55:40.467
Thursday.

55:40.467 --> 55:42.251
Hey, it's great that you guys
know the days of the week,

55:42.251 --> 55:43.644
but listen, you're
getting way too ambitious

55:43.644 --> 55:45.516
with the whole
meaning of life thing.

55:45.516 --> 55:47.256
We just need to make
sure this guy doesn't die

55:47.256 --> 55:49.346
before the sun dips
below the horizon line.

55:49.346 --> 55:52.697
[keyboard clicking]

55:52.697 --> 55:54.394
Dan, are you with us?

55:57.354 --> 55:59.225
The fuck!

55:59.225 --> 56:01.270
Someone's life is on the line,
and you're fucking around.

56:01.270 --> 56:04.317
[electronic music playing
from Dan's computer]

56:04.317 --> 56:05.318
What is this?

56:05.318 --> 56:08.147
[electronic music]

56:08.147 --> 56:09.583
This is phenomenal.

56:09.583 --> 56:10.889
Who is this?

56:10.889 --> 56:12.804
Well it's my song.

56:12.804 --> 56:14.719
I've been making it over the
past few days, it's almost--

56:14.719 --> 56:16.808
Bullshit, this isn't your song.

56:16.808 --> 56:19.550
[scoffs] Yeah it is.
It's Pro Tools, bitch.

56:19.550 --> 56:23.075
[electronic music]

56:46.577 --> 56:47.404
That's it.

56:48.535 --> 56:49.754
This is it.

56:49.754 --> 56:51.625
Vicente enjoys electronic music.

56:51.625 --> 56:53.671
Everyone enjoys
electronic music.

56:53.671 --> 56:54.498
Think about it...

56:55.977 --> 56:57.457
Even if there's one
reason, however small,

56:57.457 --> 56:59.067
why existing is better
than not existing.

56:59.067 --> 57:00.808
Why it's better to
be than not to be.

57:02.027 --> 57:03.811
One thing that makes him smile.

57:03.811 --> 57:06.074
Whoa, whoa, whoa, you're
getting way too philosophical.

57:06.074 --> 57:07.902
No, no, he's right.

57:07.902 --> 57:10.165
Given the choice between
listening to this sick song

57:10.165 --> 57:13.430
and dying, it's better to listen
to this song, much better.

57:13.430 --> 57:15.214
I'd stay alive for this.

57:15.214 --> 57:17.434
